Why would I pick Enso?[/B] Enso is not like the other servers; We are actually filled out with the flawless unique content. Enso has such a amazing utilities such as a quest system. You can trace a quest which will give you instructions. By completing quests you can achieve untradeable items. Also we can give our word that Enso won't get boring! We actually have many locations where you can go. We also have over 5 random events currently active.
[B]Enso's revision?[/B] Enso is based on the 2011 RuneScape, Enso isn't a remake though. Enso is 667 Loading 667, and doesn't contain the bugs that other server does. Enso has three very skilled and active developers maintenancing the game all of the time.
[B]What is the point of enso?[/B] -To re-create 2011 era, not a re-make but a server that has much potential to give, Enso is been very long in the development and is simply the most advanced 667, one of our biggest things is the real cache which means that Enso really is from the 2011 ERA. We are 667 loading 667. Enso is economic RuneScape private server that has insane player-killing experience aswell. We have things such as pack-yak scrolls and of course the hybrid's best pet, Wolpetinger. Enso is a stable private server which also is competely dupe & lag free. We work very hard to give the best experience for our players, that we listen to. If you would like to view some of our flawless content check out the media below.
[B]About our features[/B] We are actually filled out with features that you've never seen before. Imagine stuff like achievements system, pack yak specials, insane teleportation menu, full grand exchange and non-glitchy private server to play, best thing is we are emulating the 2011 era of RS. You definetly should atleast try Enso out. It's very addicting from the content and of course community. We are free-to-play RSPS with a huge amount of ponential.
[B]Customise Enso to Your Likings[/B] One big things in Enso is that you can customise things to your liking. You can select a home you want to use, you can select a experience rate you want to, you can customise fully your character to your liking and much more. Enso is very big for a RSPS and the developers used much maps as possible.
